## Grant Privileges to Runtime Role

### Grants Summary

| Object | Privilege | Grantee |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| `{{ dest_db | upper }}` (database) | USAGE | `{{ runtime_role | upper }}` |
| `{{ dest_db | upper }}.{{ dest_schema | upper }}` (schema) | USAGE | `{{ runtime_role | upper }}` |
| `{{ dest_db | upper }}.{{ dest_schema | upper }}` (schema) | CREATE TABLE, CREATE VIEW | `{{ runtime_role | upper }}` |
| All tables in schema | INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, SELECT | `{{ runtime_role | upper }}` |
| Future tables in schema | INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, SELECT | `{{ runtime_role | upper }}` |
| `{{ warehouse_name | upper }}` (warehouse) | USAGE | `{{ runtime_role | upper }}` |
| `JIRA_EAI` (integration) | USAGE | `{{ runtime_role | upper }}` |

> **FUTURE TABLES grant** is included to cover the `{{ dest_table | upper }}` table that the connector auto-creates on first run — without it, the connector can create the table but cannot insert data.
